	<h3>Mono no aware</h3>
	
	<blockquote cite="https://www.theschooloflife.com/thebookoflife/mono-no-aware/#:~:text=He%20wrote%3A%20'To%20know%20mono,stirred%20by%20each%20of%20them'.">
		<p>To know mono no aware is to discern the power and essence, not just of the<br> 
		moon and the cherry blossoms, but of every single thing existing in this world,<br>
		and to be stirred by each of them - <i>Motoori Norinaga</i></p>
	</blockquote>
	
		<p>Mono no aware is a Japanese philosophy describing a gentle sadness
		   at the transience of all things.  It isn't meant to be self-loathing
		   or depression but rather the observation that all phenomena passes
		   by and appreciation mixed with compassion for its transient state is
		   okay to be felt.</p>
		   
