	<h6>Wu wei</h6>
	<p><a href="http://www.taoofeastwood.com/assets/images/chapter/wu_wei.svg">Wu wei written in Chinese</a></p>
	
	<blockquote cite="https://www.goodreads.com/author/quotes/2540.Wei_Wu_Wei">
		<p>Why are you unhappy? Because 99.9 percent of everything you think, and of<br> 
		   everything you do, is for yourself—and there isn’t one. - <i>Wei Wu Wei</i></p>
	</blockquote>
	
		<p>Wu Wei is a Chinese philosophy akin to the pointlessness mentioned
		   above.  It means "non-doing" or "doing nothing" in Chinese.  However,
		   this doesn't mean laziness or profound apathy.  Quite succinctly one
		   could say that doing something to the outer world has the same effect
		   that doing nothing would.  The stream of life cannot be held back and
		   one's attempt to affect it would be as strident an attempt as doing
		   nothing to affect it.</p>
		   
